    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>Our Standards for Hosting on Stayzio</h1>
            <p>These guidelines help ensure every guest has an exceptional experience while supporting our hosts in building successful, sustainable hosting businesses. Following these standards protects both you and your guests, and helps maintain the trust that makes our platform thrive.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container">
        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">‚úÖ</div>
                <div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">Eligibility Requirements</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Who Can Host on Stayzio</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-intro">To maintain safety and trust across our platform, all hosts must meet these basic requirements:</p>

            <div class="guideline-grid">
                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üÜî">Age and Identity Verification</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Must be at least 18 years old.</li>
                        <li>Provide government-issued photo ID (driver's license, passport, or national ID).</li>
                        <li>Complete phone number verification.</li>
                        <li>Submit clear, recent photo for profile verification.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üè†">Property Authorization</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Own the property or have explicit permission from the owner.</li>
                        <li>Provide proof of ownership or written authorization.</li>
                        <li>Ensure compliance with local housing laws and HOA regulations.</li>
                        <li>Maintain current insurance coverage for short-term rentals.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üë§">Account Requirements</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>One verified account per person (no duplicate accounts).</li>
                        <li>Valid email address and active phone number.</li>
                        <li>Complete banking information for payouts.</li>
                        <li>Agree to Stayzio's Terms of Service and Host Agreement.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h4>Verification Timeline</h4>
                <p>Most verifications are completed within 24-48 hours. You can start building your listing during the verification process, but it won't go live until all requirements are met.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">üì∏</div>
                <div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">Accurate Listings</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Truth in Advertising</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-intro">Your listing is a promise to guests. Photos and descriptions must accurately represent your space to ensure guests know exactly what they're booking.</p>

            <div class="guideline-grid">
                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üì∑">Photography Standards</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Photos must be current (taken within the last 12 months).</li>
                        <li>Show the actual space guests will access.</li>
                        <li>No filters that significantly alter colors or lighting.</li>
                        <li>Include all bedrooms, bathrooms, and common areas.</li>
                        <li>Clearly show any limitations or shared spaces.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="‚úçÔ∏è">Description Accuracy</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Honest descriptions of space size and layout.</li>
                        <li>Accurate amenity listings (WiFi speed, kitchen appliances, etc.).</li>
                        <li>Clear information about parking availability.</li>
                        <li>Mention any construction, noise, or temporary issues.</li>
                        <li>Specify check-in/check-out procedures.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üìç">Location Details</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Accurate neighborhood and landmark information.</li>
                        <li>Honest walking times to public transport and attractions.</li>
                        <li>Mention any accessibility limitations.</li>
                        <li>Clarify building entry requirements (codes, keys, etc.).</li>
                        <li>Note any local regulations that might affect guests.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="example-scenario">
                <h5>Good Example:</h5>
                <p>"Cozy studio apartment on the 3rd floor (no elevator) with street parking available. Kitchen has mini-fridge and hotplate - great for light meals. 10-minute walk to downtown, 5 minutes to bus stop."</p>
            </div>

            <div class="warning-box">
                <h4>What Not to Do</h4>
                <p>Avoid using heavily filtered photos, calling a studio a "1-bedroom," or failing to mention significant limitations like construction noise or no parking.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">üåü</div>
                <div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">Guest Experience</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Communication and Hospitality Excellence</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-intro">Great hosting goes beyond providing a place to sleep. Clear communication and thoughtful touches create memorable experiences that lead to positive reviews and repeat bookings.</p>

            <div class="guideline-grid">
                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üí¨">Communication Standards</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Respond to inquiries within 24 hours (ideally within 4 hours).</li>
                        <li>Provide clear check-in instructions 24-48 hours before arrival.</li>
                        <li>Be available during guest stay for questions or issues.</li>
                        <li>Send check-out reminders and instructions.</li>
                        <li>Follow up after departure to ensure satisfaction.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üè°">Welcome Experience</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Provide a clean, welcoming space upon arrival.</li>
                        <li>Leave welcome information (WiFi, local recommendations, house rules).</li>
                        <li>Ensure all advertised amenities are working.</li>
                        <li>Stock basic essentials (toilet paper, soap, clean towels).</li>
                        <li>Maintain comfortable temperature and good lighting.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üõ†Ô∏è">Issue Resolution</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Address maintenance issues promptly.</li>
                        <li>Provide clear instructions for common problems.</li>
                        <li>Offer alternative solutions when possible.</li>
                        <li>Keep emergency contact information available.</li>
                        <li>Document and resolve complaints professionally.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="quick-checklist">
                <h4>Pre-Arrival Checklist</h4>
                <div class="checklist-grid">
                    <div class="checklist-item">Send check-in instructions.</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">Test all amenities and WiFi.</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">Stock fresh linens and towels.</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">Leave welcome guide.</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">Check cleanliness standards.</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">Confirm parking arrangements.</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="example-scenario">
                <h5>Response Time Example:</h5>
                <p>"Hi Sarah! Thanks for your inquiry about my downtown loft. Yes, it's available for your dates. The space has everything you mentioned needing, and you'll love the rooftop access. I've sent you a booking request with all the details. Let me know if you have any other questions!"</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
                <div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">Safety & Cleanliness</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Essential Standards for Guest Protection</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-intro">Guest safety is our top priority. Your property must meet basic safety requirements and maintain high cleanliness standards for every stay.</p>

            <div class="guideline-grid">
                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üîí">Security Requirements</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Secure locks on all entry points.</li>
                        <li>Working deadbolts on main entrance.</li>
                        <li>Secure windows and sliding doors.</li>
                        <li>Adequate exterior lighting for safe entry.</li>
                        <li>Clear emergency exit routes.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üî•">Fire Safety</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Working smoke detectors in all required areas.</li>
                        <li>Carbon monoxide detectors near gas appliances.</li>
                        <li>Fire extinguisher accessible and up-to-date.</li>
                        <li>Clear evacuation plan posted visibly.</li>
                        <li>No blocked emergency exits.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üßΩ">Cleanliness Standards</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Deep cleaning between every guest.</li>
                        <li>Fresh linens and towels for each stay.</li>
                        <li>Sanitized bathrooms and kitchen surfaces.</li>
                        <li>Vacuumed/mopped floors throughout.</li>
                        <li>Emptied trash and replaced bags.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üö®">Emergency Preparedness</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>First aid kit readily accessible.</li>
                        <li>Emergency contact numbers posted.</li>
                        <li>Flashlight and batteries available.</li>
                        <li>Local emergency services information.</li>
                        <li>Clear instructions for utilities shutoffs.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h4>Professional Cleaning Services</h4>
                <p>Many hosts use professional cleaning services between guests. This ensures consistent quality and saves time, especially for busy properties. Budget 15-25% of your nightly rate for professional cleaning.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="warning-box">
                <h4>Safety Violations</h4>
                <p>Properties with safety violations (non-working smoke detectors, blocked exits, unsafe electrical) may be immediately suspended until issues are resolved.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div class="section-icon">ü§ù</div>
                <div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">Respect & Conduct</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Building a Welcoming Community</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="section-intro">Stayzio is built on mutual respect and inclusivity. We expect all hosts to treat guests fairly and contribute positively to their local communities.</p>

            <div class="guideline-grid">
                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üö´">Anti-Discrimination Policy</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Welcome guests regardless of race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, or nationality.</li>
                        <li>No discriminatory language in listings or communications.</li>
                        <li>Equal treatment for all qualified guests.</li>
                        <li>Reasonable accommodation for guests with disabilities.</li>
                        <li>Report any discrimination issues immediately.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üë•">Guest Relations</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
                        <li>Maintain professional, friendly communication.</li>
                        <li>Respect guest privacy during their stay.</li>
                        <li>Honor confirmed reservations and house rules.</li>
                        <li>Handle complaints with patience and understanding.</li>
                        <li>Provide honest, helpful local recommendations.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="guideline-card">
                    <h3 data-icon="üèòÔ∏è">Community Responsibility</h3>
                    <ul class="guideline-list">
